Business Name: Southlake Orthopaedics Sports Medicine & Spine Center PC
Business Information: Dr. Thomas E. Powell, Dr. Dewey H. Jones III, and Dr. Dewey H. Jones IV are orthopedic surgeons who regard minimally invasive arthroscopic surgery, orthopedic surgery, and regenerative therapies not only as their passion, but also as their calling. Our doctors offer compassionate orthopedic care and spend ample time listening to their patients to develop customized surgical and non-surgical solutions for relieving pain, stiffness, swelling, and movement limitations. Our physicians are truly dedicated to their craft, treating people with general orthopedic conditions such as fractures, sports injuries, work-related injuries, and joint disease. In addition to performing arthroscopy, joint replacement surgery, and general orthopedic surgery, our surgeons perform surgery for the foot, ankle, hip, knee, shoulder, elbow, and wrist. Some of our physicians also administer ultrasound-guided medication injections to help relieve joint pain.

Norwood Clinic is one of the largest multispecialty medical group practices in Alabama. Located in Birmingham, Ala., the clinic has 27 physicians practicing in primary care, medical and surgical specialties. The specialties include family medicine, internal medicine, infectious diseases, nephrology, neurological/spine injury, ophthalmology, plastic/reconstructive surgery, occupational medicine, pathology pulmonary/sleep medicine, rheumatology, urology, surgery and wound care/hyperbarics. Some of the imaging procedures carried out in Norwood Clinic include CT, DEXA, echography, mammography, MRI, nerve conduction study, nuclear studies and ultrasound.

Using proprietary stretching methods and a patented strapping and stabilization system, Stretch Zone seeks to improve client health and wellness through practitioner-assisted stretching. Stretch Zone certified practitioners perform a series of dynamic stretches to increase mobility, muscle function, and active range of motion, which helps to make daily movement more efficient and effortless. A leader in the health and wellness industry, Stretch Zone has studios throughout the United States, all of which offer a welcoming and relaxing environment, experienced staff, and effective yet comfortable equipment. All studios offer the first stretch for free so you can experience the Stretch Zone Method. .

Alabama Orthopedic, Spine & Sports Medicine Associates specializes in providing personalized care. Located in Birmingham, Ala., the organization offers services in the categories of wellness, prevention, conservative treatment, education with state-of-the-art technology. It features on-site digital X-ray, digital MRI, bone density scanner handicapped accessible and in-house comprehensive physical therapy services. The group also manages special problems of the musculoskeletal system, involving diagnosis, treatment, rehabilitation and prevention. It is affiliated with the Medial Center East, Medical Center Blount and St. Clair Regional Hospital.

At OrthoAlabama Spine & Sports, with two state-of-the-art locations in Birmingham and Hoover, our specialty-trained orthopedic surgeons are dedicated experts, committed to providing you with excellence in patient-centered orthopedic care. Our orthopedic doctors proudly offer nonsurgical treatments and advanced orthopedic surgery for several areas of the body including the ankle, back, elbow, foot, hand, hip, knee, neck, shoulder, and spine. In addition to joint replacements and sports medicine.

Alabama Department of Rehabilitation Services is a state agency that is provides services to children and adults suffering from disabilities. Its children's rehabilitation service department provides assistance to teachers and school nurses in the education of children with special health care needs.   The department also hosts hemophilia program that serves individuals suffering from blood disorder. Alabama Department of Rehabilitation Services provides rehabilitation, education and employment-related services to more than 45,000 disabled individuals through partnerships with local school systems, colleges, universities and vocational technical schools. Additionally, it provides treatment for mental health diseases, and spinal cord and head injuries. Alabama Department of Rehabilitation Services is located in Montgomery, Ala.

Business Name: Southlake Orthopaedics Sports Medicine & Spine Center PC
Business Information: Dr. Thomas E. Powell, Dr. Dewey H. Jones III, and Dr. Dewey H. Jones IV are orthopedic surgeons who regard minimally invasive arthroscopic surgery, orthopedic surgery, and regenerative therapies not only as their passion, but also as their calling. Our doctors offer compassionate orthopedic care and spend ample time listening to their patients to develop customized surgical and non-surgical solutions for relieving pain, stiffness, swelling, and movement limitations. Our physicians are truly dedicated to their craft, treating people with general orthopedic conditions such as fractures, sports injuries, work-related injuries, and joint disease. In addition to performing arthroscopy, joint replacement surgery, and general orthopedic surgery, our surgeons perform surgery for the foot, ankle, hip, knee, shoulder, elbow, and wrist. Some of our physicians also administer ultrasound-guided medication injections to help relieve joint pain.

Jones IV are orthopedic surgeons who regard minimally invasive arthroscopic surgery, orthopedic surgery, and regenerative therapies not only as their passion, but also as their calling. Our doctors offer compassionate orthopedic care and spend ample time listening to their patients to develop customized surgical and non-surgical solutions for relieving pain, stiffness, swelling, and movement limitations. Our physicians are truly dedicated to their craft, treating people with general orthopedic conditions such as fractures, sports injuries, work-related injuries, and joint disease. Some of our physicians also administer ultrasound-guided medication injections to help relieve joint pain.
